description: 1978 Wooden Schooner -  PROJECT BOAT LOA: 64.8 Beam: 20.4 Draft: 7.4 Gross Ton. 62 This project is not for the faint of heart. She's a good ship, with a long beautiful history.  We came upon her with the intention of finishing her conversion into a Pirate ship, but our backers left us high and dry. Frame is made from White Oak, Outer planking is Mohogony. Inside is Cypress. She's in dire need of some TLC, as the owners previous to the ones we bought her from left her to rot. Previous owners did some repairs and sailed her from Jacksonville to St. Augustine. Frame is solid, but she is in need of a refit.  Keel was replaced previous to our purchase of her, and Original construction plans, our refit plans, pictures (digital) of when she was built at Mystic Seaport back in 1977-78, all noted and historical data, as well as our survey report (7/2016) are included in this sale. Other items included in the sale are mohogany planks of various sizes (under tarps below her), a GM Detroit Diesel 4-71 (original engine to the ship), spare gearbox, new 3" shaft (installed, packed, and sealed previous to purchase). She has been in Drydock for the past 2 years at the SAMC, previously was known as "Voyager" and now known as "Pursuit" (Re-named by previous owners). Asking what we paid for her ($45,000) Or Best Offer, and we are still taking a loss at the asking price.  Lowball offers will be completely ignored.
